随着疫情消息的增多，各种关于其来源、如何传播与防控的“传言”也接踵而来。
As the spread of the epidemic has increased, so have the "rumors" about its origin, how it is spread and how it is controlled.
为此，我们采访了相关领域的专业人士，试图解答十个公众最为关心的问题。
To this end, we interviewed professionals in the field and tried to answer ten of the most important public concerns.
记者 | 许冰清肖文杰倪妮张云亭项维肖 毛怡玫实习记者 | 文思敏数据整理 | 实习记者 袁颖图表制作| 程星 王方宏发源于武汉的新型冠状病毒疫情仍在蔓延。
Reporters & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45;
截至1月23日24点，全国新型冠状病毒感染肺炎已确诊830例。
As of 24: 00 on January 23, 830 cases of new coronavirus-infected pneumonia have been diagnosed nationwide.
而可能稍微值得宽慰的一点是，从1月20日开始，中国各地终于开始日益重视这起疫情了。
And, perhaps somewhat reassuringly, since January 20, China has finally begun to pay increasing attention to the epidemic.
1月22日的上海虹桥火车站内，不少春运旅客都选择了佩戴口罩。
At Shanghai Hongqiao Railway Station on January 22, many Spring Festival couriers chose to wear masks.
|摄影：王一越不过随着疫情消息的增多，各种关于其来源、如何传播与防控的“传言”也接踵而来。
Photo: Wang Yue has only just added to the growing body of information about its origin, how it was spread and controlled.
为此，《第一财经》YiMagazine采访了研究病毒基因组的科研人员、流行病专家、公共卫生研究者、卫健委内部人士以及城市科学研究者茅明睿等各领域人士，试图解答十个你最为关心，但可能仍充满疑惑的问题。
To that end, First Finance Yi Magazine interviewed researchers working on viral genomes, epidemiologists, public health researchers, health-care insiders, and urban science researcher Mao MingRui, trying to answer ten questions that you most care about but may still be full of doubts.
01遇到这样的传染病疫情，中国的医疗体系应该怎么运转起来？应对传染病的体系由许多部门组成。
How should China's healthcare system function in the face of such an epidemic? The system for dealing with infectious diseases is made up of many departments.
各级疾控中心（疾病预防控制中心）可能是其中的核心。
CDC levels (Centers for Disease Control and Prevention) may be at the heart of this.
它是一个由政府全资拨款的事业单位，各级卫健委所属。
It is a wholly-owned government-funded institution, under the health care committee at all levels.
应对传染病是它的重要职责。
It has an important responsibility to deal with infectious diseases.
它有技术力量，有可以检测病原体的实验室，也有从事流行病学调查的专业人员。
It has technical capacity, laboratories where pathogens can be detected, and professionals who conduct epidemiological investigations.
如果出现传染病疫情，处理方式大致是这样的：1）医生发现法定传染病；2）医院通过网络系统上报给地方疾控中心；3）疾控中心会派流行病学的调查人员，了解接触史等信息；4）调查人员还会采集病人的样本，让专业的实验室分析病原；5）调查和检测的结果都会形成报告，再报给卫健委；6）一般的传染病可能到此为止，但如果事情更严重，可能会触发相关预案。
In the event of an infectious disease outbreak, the treatment is basically as follows: 1) the doctor detects a statutory infectious disease; 2) the hospital reports to the local CDC through a network system; 3) the CDC sends epidemiological investigators to study the history of exposure; 4) the results of the investigation and testing are reported to the CHRC.
如果要调动医院的床位、医生、增加防护、隔离、转移病人，这些事情就不归疾控中心负责了。
If the hospital beds, doctors, additional protection, isolation, transfer patients, these matters are not the responsibility of the CDC.
卫健委会通过专门管理医院的医政处下发通知；7）当出现值得注意的异常状况，卫健委会很快抽调全国的相关专家，成立专家组，他们会直接向政府提出各方面的处理建议。
The Health and Wellness Commission issues circulars through the Department of Medicine, which specializes in the management of hospitals. 7) When unusual circumstances arise that warrant attention, the Health and Wellness Commission quickly draws on relevant experts from all over the country to set up a panel of experts who will make recommendations directly to the Government on various aspects of the treatment.
就像这次这样。
Just like this one.
各地政府编制的应对公共卫生事件的预案中，都考虑到了新传染病和尚未发现的传染病情况，但这种情况下，能否及时上报、调查和处置，更多就靠医疗体系和当地政府的经验和执行能力。
New infectious diseases and undetected infectious diseases are taken into account in plans prepared by local governments to respond to public health events, but in such cases timely reporting, investigation and disposal depend more on the experience and implementation capacity of health systems and local governments.
这时，反应速度就成了关键。
At this point, speed of response becomes the key.
02如果我身处医院的发热门诊，医院将如何降低我的被感染概率？首先，医院会强化清洁消毒管理的工作，比如加强诊疗环境的通风。
If I am in a hospital's fever clinic, how will the hospital reduce my risk of infection? First, the hospital will step up its cleaning and disinfection management, such as enhancing ventilation in the clinical setting.
有条件的医疗机构会实行空气消毒，也可配备循环风空气消毒设备。
Conditional medical institutions will carry out air disinfection, may also be equipped with circulating air disinfection equipment.
对诊疗环境、医疗器械、患者用物等也都会做清洁消毒。
Diagnosis and treatment of the environment, medical equipment, patients will also do cleaning and disinfection.
其次，医院应该尽量减少患者的拥挤，以减少医院感染的风险。
Second, hospitals should minimize overcrowding in order to reduce the risk of hospital infections.
发现疑似或确诊感染新型冠状病毒的患者时，依法采取隔离或者控制传播措施，并按照规定对患者的陪同人员和其他密切接触人员采取医学观察，以及其他必要的预防措施。
When a patient suspected or confirmed to be infected with a new coronavirus is found, measures shall be taken to isolate or control the transmission of the coronavirus in accordance with the law, and medical observation and other necessary preventive measures shall be taken against the escort and other persons in close contact with the patient.
不具备救治能力的时候，及时将患者转诊到具备救治能力的医疗机构。
When the ability of treatment is not available, timely referral to a medical institution with treatment capacity.
近期，医疗机构还会帮助就诊患者及其陪同人员积极了解新型冠状病毒防护知识教育，指导其正确洗手、咳嗽礼仪和居家隔离等。
Recently, medical institutions will also help patients and their escorts to actively understand the new coronavirus protection education, guide them to wash their hands correctly, cough etiquette and home isolation.
03我们经历过SARS了，有什么经验是对这次疫情的处置有帮助的？现在中国的传染病防治体系，基本是在2003年的SARS疫情后建立起来的。
We have experienced SARS, what experience has helped us to deal with this epidemic? Now China's infectious disease control system was basically set up after the SARS epidemic in 2003.
《传染病防治法》是在2004年实施的。
The Communicable Diseases Act was introduced in 2004.
在其中，第一次确定了几个重要原则，比如所有医院的传染病病例，都必须上报卫生部门，而此前，军队所属医院没有这个义务；又比如，在这部法律中，第一次提出了“乙类传染病，采取甲类传染病的预防、控制措施”的方法，这确保了对新型传染病能采取足够强有力的防控措施。
For the first time, several important principles have been identified, such as that all cases of infectious diseases in hospitals must be reported to the health sector, whereas previously military hospitals were not obliged to do so; for example, the law for the first time introduced the method of "prevention and control measures for Class B infectious diseases," which ensures strong enough control measures against new infectious diseases.
这次的新型冠状病毒感染的肺炎，也是按照此标准。
This time the new coronavirus infection of pneumonia is also in accordance with this standard.
另外，在2003年之后，中国政府的医疗卫生支出增幅迅速增加。
Moreover, after 2003, the government's health-care spending increased rapidly.
2003年是1116亿元，2018年时比这个数字翻了13倍。
The figure was 111.6 billion yuan in 2003 and 13 times that figure in 2018.
*卫生总费用＝政府卫生支出＋社会卫生支出＋个人卫生支出卫生总费用、政府卫生支出等定义及计算方式详见>>国家统计局卫生和社会服务指标解释如今，每个省市会有专门的接收传染病患者的医院。
:: Total health expenditure = government spending on health + spending on hygiene + total health expenditure, government health spending, and how it is defined and calculated. & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & # 160; & # 160; & # 160; & # 160; & # 160; & # 160; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & # 45; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp; & # 160; & nbsp; & nbsp; & nbsp;
平时，它们会收治各类病人，而当其他医院出现了特定的传染病时，一般会转诊到这里，以及其他定点医院，比如肺结核、艾滋病等。
They treat a wide range of patients and are referred to other hospitals for specific infections, as well as to other designated hospitals, such as tuberculosis and AIDS.
而当出现了像SARS这样的疫情时，它可以第一时间建立起隔离病房。
And when there is an outbreak like SARS, it can set up the isolation ward in the first place.
比如上海的公共卫生中心，它就是在SARS疫情后建立的，医院内的草坪下都埋好了管道，应急的时候可以直接搭起板房当临时病房，用来集中隔离治疗。
Shanghai's public-health center, for example, was built after the SARS epidemic, with pipes laid under the hospital's lawns, and a makeshift ward that can be used for centralized quarantine when needed.
04到现在为止，我们面临的情况比SARS时期更严重吗？传染病的疫情传播是个充满变量的模型。
So far, are we facing a more serious situation than we faced during the SARS period? The spread of infectious disease is a variable model.
疾病本身的传播属性、所在地的人员密度、人员流动情况、防治措施的采取时间、天气都会产生影响。
The nature of the spread of the disease itself, the density of people in the area, the movement of people, the timing of interventions, and the weather all have an impact.
所以没法完全类比，但有几个时间点可以参考。
So there is no complete analogy, but there are a few points in time to look at.
所有传染病的防治都可以靠“三板斧”解决：1）控制传染源；2）切断传播途径；3）保护易感人群。
All infectious diseases can be treated with a "triple ax": 1) control the source of infection; 2) cut off transmission routes; and 3) protect vulnerable populations.
这三件事，每件都是越早做到越好。
The earlier you do each of these three things, the better.
在第一件事上，这次我们的动作比SARS时候快。
The first thing we did this time was faster than SARS.
12月30日，武汉卫健委医政医管处发布《关于做好不明原因肺炎救治工作的紧急通知》，称12月以来，武汉开始出现不明原因的肺炎。
On December 30, Wuhan Health Commission Medical and Medical Administration issued the "Emergency Notice on the Treatment of Unknown Causes of Pneumonia," saying that since December, Wuhan began to appear unknown causes of pneumonia.
1月7日，疾控中心的专家已经分离出了新型冠状病毒；1月10日，复旦大学公共卫生中心的张永振教授团队就在全球病毒研究的学术网站上发布了病毒的全基因组序列。
On January 7, CDC experts isolated the new coronavirus, and on January 10, a team of professors Zhang Yongzhen of the Fudan University Center for Public Health published a genome-wide sequence of the virus on the global virus research academic website.
也就是说，从疾病出现，到确认病原体，只用了不到1个月的时间。
That is, from the onset of the disease to the identification of pathogens, it took less than a month.
而SARS疫情，用了5个月，才由国外的科学家检测出冠状病毒，并由世卫组织确认其为病原体。
The SARS outbreak took five months for scientists from abroad to detect the coronavirus, which WHO identified as the pathogen.
接下来，就是针对病原体和疾病的特性，迅速防控了。
Then there are the characteristics of pathogens and diseases, which are quickly controlled.
这不单是医疗卫生体系的事，因为信息公开、疫情管控、动员等工作，需要政府统筹来完成。
This is not just a matter for the health system, because information disclosure, disease control and mobilization efforts need to be coordinated by the Government.
但1月11日开始，武汉市卫健委发布的确诊病例就一直是41例，直到1月16日，升至45例。
But since Jan. 11, the number of confirmed cases from Wuhan Health Commission has been 41, rising to 45 as of January 16.
1月20日，中国卫健委将这个疾病纳入了法定传染病范围。
On January 20, the Chinese health committee added the disease to the list of legal infectious diseases.
Play▲记者：第一财经 吴绵强05“武汉肺炎”在波及全国之前，为什么没有先在湖北省境内爆发？关于这个问题，城市象限创始人兼CEO 、北京市城市规划设计研究院云平台创新中心秘书长茅明睿及其团队通过2018年至2019年的“腾讯迁徙数据”与其他数据的综合研究，给出了一些有意思的讨论视角——1）湖北省内各市，以及岳阳、信阳、九江等湖北周边地市，都应该加强对来自“武汉都市圈”（注：以武汉为中心，覆盖黄石、鄂州、黄冈、孝感、咸宁、仙桃、潜江、天门等周边8个大中型城市所组成的城市群）的长途大巴乘客的排查。
Wu Mianqiang 05 "Wuhan Pneumonia" Before affecting the whole country, why did not the first explosion in Hubei Province? On this issue, city quadrant founder and CEO Mao MingRui, Secretary-General of the Cloud Platform Innovation Center of Beijing Institute of Urban Planning and Design and other data.
这是因为，都市圈内的城市跟中心城市有日常的高频联系，甚至是通勤联系。
This is because the city within the metropolitan area has daily high-frequency connections, even commuting links, with the central city.
但在目前湖北省披露的疫情数字中，只报告了黄冈市的情况，所以湖北省内疫情存在着被低估或者未被有效统计的可能性。
However, only Huanggang city has been reported in the current epidemic figures in Hubei Province, so there is a possibility that the epidemic situation in Hubei Province is underestimated or not effectively counted.
2）北京、上海、成都、广州、长沙、襄阳、荆州、宜昌等城市，应该加强排查来自于武汉的铁路客源；北京、昆明、沈阳、成都等城市，还要加强排查来自武汉的航班。
2) In cities such as Beijing, Shanghai, Chengdu, Guangzhou, Changsha, Xiangyang, Jingzhou and Yichang, the number of rail passengers coming from Wuhan should be strengthened.
在这些城市中，长沙、昆明都是与武汉联系度较高、但目前疫情人数还比较少的新一线城市。
Among these cities, Changsha and Kunming are new first-tier cities with high links to Wuhan but few epidemic numbers.
这两个城市又是各自都市圈的中心城市，也是城市群的重要节点，所以这两个城市如果暴发疫情，存在一定的扩散能力。
These two cities are the center of their metropolitan area and important nodes of urban agglomerations, so there is a certain capacity to spread if outbreaks occur in these two cities.
3）被“武汉肺炎”扩散到的北京、上海、广州、深圳这几个一线城市，医疗条件好，信息透明度高，以及有抗非典的经验，民众自我防护意识也很高，所以情况相对乐观。
3) The spread of Wuhan Pneumonia to the first tier cities of Beijing, Shanghai, Guangzhou and Shenzhen, with good medical conditions, high levels of information transparency, and SARS experience, as well as a high level of self-defense awareness, the situation is relatively optimistic.
在介绍目前的这一分析结果之外，茅明睿还特别强调，目前疫区一定要披露细致的公开数据，这样才能有效增加疫区所在地市民的自我防护意识。
In addition to presenting the results of the current analysis, Mao also stressed that the current epidemic area must disclose detailed open data, so as to effectively increase the local people's awareness of self-defense.
而目前按照省来公开数据的做法，既不利于市民防护，又不利于各界做出适当的应对，也不利于学者开展有价值的研究。
The current practice of making data publicly available by province is not only detrimental to public protection, but also to appropriate responses and valuable research by scholars.
