2007-9-25 21: 48 How much longer will it take for the vaccine to go from research and development to the market and then to consumers to reach consumers? When SARS broke out, Mr. Zhong proposed the hormone-impact therapy, which was widely used in SARS emergency treatment.
但这也导致很多患者病愈后出现股骨头坏死症状，以及产生肺部功能障碍和其他药物副作用反应。
But it also causes necrosis of the femoral head and lung dysfunction and other side effects of drugs in many patients.
在获得新型冠状病毒的基因组序列后，目前，美国包括卫生研究院、休斯顿贝勒医学院，以及得克萨斯、纽约等团队，加拿大萨斯喀彻温大学，以及中国的一个科学家团队都已经开始着手研发相应疫苗。
With the new coronavirus genome sequence now available, teams from the US, including the Institut of Health Sciences, Baylor College of Medicine in Houston, and teams from Texas and New York, the University of Saskatchewan in Canada, and a team of Chinese scientists have all begun to develop vaccines.
贝勒医学院的疫苗科学家彼得·霍特兹表示，“冠状病毒是一个相对简单的疫苗靶点。
"The coronavirus is a relatively simple vaccine target," said Peter Hotez, a vaccine scientist at Baylor College of Medicine.
”所以，其研发难度要低于针对艾滋病病毒或流感等其他病毒的疫苗。
So it is less difficult to develop than vaccines against other viruses, such as HIV or flu.
疫苗开发完成后，预计还要用几个月时间做第一阶段临床试验，正式投放市场要等到一年多以后。
After the vaccine is developed, it is expected to take several months to complete the first phase of clinical trials, and it will take more than a year for the vaccine to go on the market.
072020年的新型冠状病毒，和SARS病毒相比“新”在何处？此前我们已知的人类冠状病毒共有六种：其中四种冠状病毒在人群中较为常见，致病性较低；另外两种就是SARS冠状病毒和MERS冠状病毒，都可引起严重的呼吸系统疾病。
Where is the new coronavirus in 2007-2020 compared to the SARS coronavirus? There are six previously known coronavirus in humans: four coronavirus are common and less pathogenic in the population; the other two coronavirus SARS coronavirus and MERS coronavirus can cause severe respiratory disease.
此次发现的新型冠状病毒，不同于已发现的所有人类冠状病毒。
This discovery of a new coronavirus, different from all the human coronavirus has been found.
2020年1月10日，复旦大学的张永振教授团队在科研网站virological.org首次公布了武汉新型冠状病毒基因组序列。
On January 10, 2020, Professor Zhang Yongzhen of Fudan University released the first genome sequence of Wuhan coronavirus on the scientific research website virological.
基于该基因组序列，中国科学院上海巴斯德研究所郝沛研究员及其团队于1月21日发布了一项名为《武汉新型冠状病毒进化来源和传染人分子作用通路》的研究成果。
Based on the genome sequence, Hao Pepi, a researcher at the Pasteur Institute of the Chinese Academy of Sciences in Shanghai, and his team released a study on January 21 called "The Evolution of Wuhan's New Coronavirus and Pathways to Infection Human Molecules."
在该论文里，郝沛研究员及其团队揭示了新型冠状病毒的进化来源，以及该病毒与SARS冠状病毒、MERS冠状病毒之间存在着遗传进化关系。
In this paper, Hao Pui researchers and his team revealed the evolutionary origin of the new coronavirus and the genetic relationship between the virus and SARS coronavirus and MERS coronavirus.
新型冠状病毒与SARS病毒的致病机制也类同，都是一种免疫病理反应——当病毒进入体内后，病毒会寄生在活细胞内，诱使人体的免疫细胞开始攻击自己的细胞，由此导致严重的炎症反应。
The new coronavirus, which is similar to the SARS virus, is an immunopathological response. When the virus enters the body, it will infect living cells, inducing the body's immune cells to attack their own cells, leading to a serious inflammatory response.
08新型冠状病毒到底从哪来，它的传染性和变异性如何？2003年“SARS”爆发后，研究者们发现SARS冠状病毒的传播途径是“蝙蝠-果子狸-人”，而后国际社会发现蝙蝠是冠状病毒的大本营。
After the SARS outbreak in 2003, researchers discovered that the transmission route of the coronavirus is "bat-civet-man," and the bat was found to be the base of the coronavirus.
此次，郝沛团队通过将新型冠状病毒、SARS冠状病毒与MERS冠状病毒做全基因组比对发现，这几种病毒有着共同的祖先。
This time, Hao Pai's team identified the coronavirus, SARS coronavirus and MERS coronavirus as a genome-wide comparison and found that the viruses have a common ancestor.
由此推测，武汉冠状病毒的自然宿主也可能是蝙蝠。
It is speculated that the natural host of Wuhan coronavirus may also be bats.
1月22日，北京大学、广西中医药大学、宁波大学等机构在Journal of MedicalVirology 杂志上联合发表的论文则认为，蛇是造成当前武汉新型冠状病毒2019-nCoV感染爆发的最可能的野生动物库。
According to a paper published in the Journal of Medicine on January 22 by Peking University, Guangxi TCM University and Ningbo University, the snake is the most likely wildlife bank to cause the current Wuhan coronavirus 2019-nCoV outbreak.
也就是说，此次新型冠状病毒，可能经历了从“蝙蝠-蛇-人”的传播路径。
In other words, this new coronavirus, may have undergone a "bat-snake-human" transmission route.
通过郝沛团队的研究我们发现，新型冠状病毒与SARS病毒的致病机制类同，新型冠状病毒是通过S-蛋白与人ACE2相互作用，来感染人的呼吸道上皮细胞，这意味着从病毒角度提供了可人传人的依据。
Through Hao's research, we found that the new coronavirus is similar to the pathogenic mechanism of SARS virus. The new coronavirus is infected with human respiratory epithelial cells through S-protein interaction with human ACE2, which means it provides a basis for human-to-human transmission from a viral perspective.
钟南山院士在接受央视新闻频道《新闻1+1》栏目采访时，向公众确认了新型冠状病毒会“人传人”。
Academician Zhong Nan Shan in the CCTV news channel "news 1 + 1" column interview, confirmed to the public that the new coronavirus will "human-to-human."
1月21日，世界卫生组织官员在接受《新京报》采访时仍表示，最新报告的感染信息“目前尚无明确的证据表明（新型冠状病毒可以）持续人传人”。
In an interview with the Beijing News on January 21, World Health Organization officials said the newly reported infection "does not yet have clear evidence that the coronavirus can continue to be passed from person to person."
按照长期研究病毒性新发性传染病的香港大学公共卫生学院副教授朱华晨的说法，就是“毒传一两代就断了”，难以实现高效传播，甚至超级传播。
According to Zhu Huachen, an associate professor at the University of Hong Kong School of Public Health, who has long studied viral new infectious diseases, "a generation or two of virulence is dead," making efficient transmission or even super-transmission difficult.
而在1月22日公布最新病例数据时，国家卫健委副主任李斌表示，新型冠状病毒还存在变异的可能。
When the latest case data was released on January 22, Li Bin, deputy director of the National Health Council, said the new coronavirus could still mutate.
当地时间1月22日上午，世界卫生组织在日内瓦召开了紧急情况委员会会议。
On the morning of January 22, the World Health Organization (WHO) held a meeting of the Emergency Committee in Geneva.
经过两日讨论，世卫组织在当地时间1月23日晚、北京时间1月24日凌晨举行的新闻发布会上宣布，目前暂时不会将新型冠状病毒肺炎疫情界定为“国际关注的突发公共卫生事件”。
After two days of discussions, WHO announced at a press conference on the evening of January 23, local time and the early hours of January 24, Beijing time, that it would not define the new coronavirus pneumonia as a "public health emergency of international concern."
而根据《国际卫生条例》的定义，“国际公共卫生紧急事件”是指“通过疾病的国际传播构成对其它国家的公共卫生风险”，并可能需要采取协调一致的“国际应对措施”的“不同寻常”的事件。
The IHR defines an "international public health emergency" as "an" extraordinary "event that" poses a public health risk to other countries through the international spread of disease, "and may require a coordinated" international response. "
自2000年代中期实施该规则以来，仅就甲型H1N1流感、脊髓灰质炎疫情、埃博拉疫情和“寨卡”疫情宣布了五次。
Since the adoption of the Code in the mid-2000s, only five announcements have been made concerning influenza A (H1N1), polio, Ebola and Zika.
09此前有研究机构预测新型冠状病毒肺炎在武汉的已感染人数在数千人级别，是否可信？目前，交通数据、移动通信数据与社交媒体数据等非传统公共卫生数据都可以用来辅助测算乃至预测流行病的疫情风险。
09 Previous research has predicted that the number of people infected with the new coronavirus pneumonia in Wuhan is now in the thousands, and that non-traditional public health data, such as traffic data, mobile data and social media data, can be used to help measure and even predict the risk of an epidemic.
在此次新型冠状病毒肺炎的相关疫情预测中，英国帝国理工学院的MRC全球传染病分析中心与香港大学公共卫生学院都是使用了武汉交通数据作为关键的建模依据。
Both the Centre for Global Infectious Disease Analysis (MRC) of Imperial College of Technology and the School of Public Health of the University of Hong Kong (HKU) used Wuhan traffic data as a key basis for modelling the new coronavirus pneumonia.
在MRC的研究方法中，主要是利用境外通报的已确诊病例，来反推武汉市内的情况，关键的模型参数有4个：境外已确诊病例数、每天从武汉机场出境的旅客数、武汉机场每日旅客数，以及病毒的平均潜伏期。
In the research methods of MRC, the key parameters of the model are four: the number of confirmed cases abroad, the number of passengers departing Wuhan airport every day, the number of passengers per day at Wuhan airport, and the average incubation period of the virus.
这4个参数的数据本身有一定的弹性（比如病毒潜伏期一般估算为10天，但也有可能是8天），所以测算出的已感染人数是一个很大的范围。
The data for these four parameters are inherently elastic (for example, the incubation period of the virus is generally estimated to be 10 days, but may also be 8 days), so the number of infected persons calculated is a large one.
利用1月18日政府的通报数据，MRC给出1月18日武汉的感染人数最大上下限范围分别为1000至9700人，标准参数下预测最大可能值为4000人。
Using government data from the 18 January notification, the MRC gave a maximum range of 1,000 to 9,700 for Wuhan on January 18 and a maximum of 4,000 for the standard parameters.
（MRC报告详见>>News / Wuhan Coronavirus）在1月22日的国务院办公室新闻发布会上，中国科学院院士、中国疾病预防控制中心主任高福对这一研究结果回应称：“大家知道，认识任何一个新生事物，尤其像这样的病毒，一定是‘事实是事实，知识理论是理论’。
(See MRC report at & gt; News / Wuhan Coronavirus, a member of the Chinese Academy of Sciences and director of the China Centers for Disease Control and Prevention, at a press conference at the State Council's office on 22 January.
……我想随着大家对这个病毒的认识，会去验证这个模型。
I think that as you get to know the virus, you will test the model.
目前我们掌握的情况，并不是这位科学家计算的模型情况。
What we have now is not the model that the scientist has calculated.
”香港大学公共卫生学院1月21日发布的数学模型与MRC类似，利用的是1月17日政府的通报数据，并综合考虑了飞机、火车和公路运输的情况，推测出当日武汉的感染人数最大可能值为1343人，而武汉以外的其他省市最多有可能出现300则感染个案。
Similar to the MRC, the mathematical model released on January 21 by the Faculty of Public Health of the University of Hong Kong draws on government data from January 17 and combines air, rail and road transport to estimate the highest possible number of infections in Wuhan on that day at 1,343, with up to 300 in other provinces and cities outside Wuhan.
香港大学公共卫生医学讲座教授梁卓伟在1月21日同时表示，这一模型考虑到了近日武汉市和全球各城市的防疫措施，以病毒传播力较初期减75%为依据做乐观估算，到大年初七，国外将会增加1-2个感染个案，国内除武汉外其他省市感染个案最高可能增加70个。
A spokesman for the Department of Health said today (January 21) that the model took into account the anti-epidemic measures in Wuhan city and other cities around the world. Based on the initial 75% reduction in transmission rate of the virus, foreign countries will increase 1-2 cases by the end of the year.
但目前，香港大学公共卫生学院网站对于这则研究的相关披露已经增加了一条说明：“由于境外通报病例数在24小时内增加一倍，报告的研究已经不再有效，正在重新调整模型。
But a note has been added to the study published on the website of the University of Hong Kong's School of Public Health: "As the number of notified cases outside the country doubles within 24 hours, the reported research is no longer valid and the model is being readjusted."
”（香港大学公共卫生学院报告详见>>HKUMed ）10在救治病人的过程中，医护人员又该如何保护自己？根据不同的接触情形，医护人员要采取不同的防护措施：比如接触患者的血液、体液、分泌物、排泄物、呕吐物及污染物品时，须戴清洁手套，脱手套后洗手。
(For details about the HKU School of Public Health report, see & gt; HKUMed) & # 160; & # 160; How should healthcare personnel protect themselves during treatment? Depending on the exposure situation, health personnel should take different precautions: wear clean gloves and wash hands after handling blood, body fluids, secretions, excreta, vomit and contaminants.
可能受到患者血液、体液、分泌物等喷溅时，要戴医用防护口罩、护目镜，穿防体液渗入的长袖隔离衣，戴手套。
May be the patient's blood, body fluids, secretions and other spatter, to wear medical masks, goggles, body fluids infiltration of the long-sleeve isolation clothing, wearing gloves.
为疑似患者或确诊患者做如气管插管、无创通气、气管切开、心肺复苏、支气管镜检查等检查动作时，要采取空气隔离措施——佩戴医用防护口罩，并做密闭性能检测；眼部要戴好护目镜或面罩；穿防体液渗入的长袖隔离衣，戴手套；此外，操作应在通风良好的房间内；房间中人数限制在患者所需护理和支持的最低数量。
For suspected or confirmed patients, air isolation measures such as endotracheal intubation, non-invasive ventilation, tracheotomy, cardiopulmonary resuscitation, bronchoscopy, eye protection with goggles or masks, long-sleeved sealant jackets with gloves; well-ventilated rooms; and limited to the minimum number of patients requiring care and support.
以上所有防护用品一旦被患者血液、体液、分泌物等污染，就要及时更换。
All the above-mentioned protective equipment should be replaced as soon as the patient's blood, body fluid, secretion and other pollution.
诊疗疑似或确诊患者的听诊器、体温计、血压计等医疗器具及护理物品也应是专人专用，或在每次使用后应做规范的清洁和消毒。
Medical devices such as stethoscopes, thermometers, sphygmomanometers, and care products for patients with suspected or confirmed illness should also be used for personal use or should be properly cleaned and disinfected after each use.
最后，医疗机构还应合理调配人力资源和班次安排，避免医务人员过度劳累。
Finally, medical institutions should rationally allocate human resources and shift schedules to avoid overwork by medical staff.
提供营养膳食，增强免疫力。
Provide nutritious meals to strengthen immunity.
针对岗位特点和风险评估结果，开展主动健康监测，包括体温和呼吸系统症状等。
Active health monitoring, including body temperature and respiratory symptoms, is carried out in response to job characteristics and risk assessment results.
一定要保护好自己！| 题图来源：人民日报官方微博。
Be sure to protect yourself! & # 160; Source: People's Daily official Weibo.
图中为武汉大学人民医院呼吸与危重症医学科医生张旃副教授（中）与她的同事。
Chandrake Chandrake, an associate professor of respiratory and critically ill medicine at Wuhan University's People's Hospital, and her colleagues.
